        {
            "text": "Water deficit usually inhibits plant growth and pro ductivity by affecting gas exchange and especially pho tosynthesis [6, 7] . Water use efficiency (WUE) can be traditionally defined as the ratio of net photosynthesis to transpiration over a period of seconds or minutes [8] . The higher WUE has been mentioned as a strategy 1 This text was submitted by the authors in English.",
